---
// Import necessary components and assets
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";

// Define placeholder image paths (replace with actual paths later)
import heroImg from "../../assets/LandingImage.jpg"; // Keep existing header or use a generic one
import BlogImgPlaceholder from "../../assets/blogImages/blog10.webp"; // Placeholder for main blog image
import LocalProducePlaceholder from "../../assets/blogImages/blog8.webp"; // Placeholder for inline image

// Define Breadcrumbs for this specific blog post
const breadcrumbs = [
    { label: "Home", href: "/" },
    { label: "Blogs", href: "/blogs" },
    { label: "Sustainable Dining in India", href: "#", current: true } // Updated breadcrumb
];

// Structure the blog post content based on the DOCX file
const blogData = {
    // Metadata from DOCX
    title: "From Farm to Table: The Importance of Sustainable Dining in India",
    metaTitle: "Sustainable Dining in India: Farm-to-Table at Vanchu Hut",
    metaDescription: "Discover sustainable dining at Vanchu Hut! Explore the best food in Ghaziabad while supporting local farmers and enjoying fresh, eco-friendly meals.",
    
    // Use placeholder for the main blog image
    image: BlogImgPlaceholder, 
    
    // Set a relevant publish date
    publishDate: "2025-04-11", // Example date, adjust as needed

    // Introduction section
    introduction: "Sustainable dining is more than just a trend; it’s a movement changing how we eat, especially in India. With rising awareness about environmental sustainability, health, and social responsibility, diners are looking for more than just good food. They're seeking meals that tell a story—from farm to table. The focus keyword here is “sustainable dining,” because it perfectly aligns with what conscious consumers care about today. This blog looks at the importance of sustainable dining in India. It shows how restaurants like Vanchu Hut are making a positive impact. They do this by sourcing local food and focusing on fresh, ethically produced ingredients.",

    // Main content sections based on DOCX structure
    sections: [
        {
            title: "The Rise of Sustainable Dining in India",
            content: "India is witnessing a significant shift in consumer dining preferences. A report by Dineout shows that about 75% of Indian diners now prefer restaurants that use eco-friendly practices. This includes sourcing local ingredients, reducing food waste, and using biodegradable packaging. More Indian millennials and Gen Z consumers are becoming aware of climate change. They understand how it affects resources. This trend is growing among these groups. By choosing sustainable dining options, Indian foodies are playing their part in fostering a greener, healthier planet."
        },
        {
            title: "What is \"Farm to Table\"?",
            content: "The \"farm-to-table\" idea means serving food that is grown nearby, freshly picked, and not heavily processed. This ethos not only reduces the carbon footprint—transporting goods over long distances can cause pollution—but it also helps the local economy grow by supporting farmers and small agricultural businesses. When restaurants use the farm-to-table approach, they focus on fresher ingredients. This means diners get higher-quality meals with real flavors. It’s a win-win for everyone involved, from the hands that sow the seeds to those that savor the dishes."
        },
        {
            title: "How Vanchu Hut Supports Local Farmers",
            // Include bullet points using Markdown list format within the content string
            content: `At Vanchu Hut, sustainability isn’t just a marketing buzzword; it’s a mission. We are proud to be one of the best Chinese restaurants in Ghaziabad. We also use local, sustainable ingredients in many of our dishes. 

Here’s how we support the farm-to-table movement:
1.   **Partnering With Local Growers:** By collaborating with farmers in and around Ghaziabad, we ensure our vegetables and spices are as fresh as possible.
2.   **Minimizing Food Miles:** Many of the ingredients used in signature dishes like our Veg Manchurian and Special Veg Noodles are sourced within a 50-kilometer radius of the restaurant.
3.   **Seasonal Menus:** We design our offerings based on what’s in season, ultimately reducing reliance on long-term refrigeration and imported goods.

This not only ensures fresher food but also lets our customers feel part of something bigger with every bite.`,
            // Add placeholder image reference for this section
            image: LocalProducePlaceholder, 
            imageAlt: "Placeholder image showing fresh local produce"
        },
        {
            title: "Benefits of Sustainable Dining",
             // Include numbered list using Markdown format within the content string
            content: `
1.  **Healthier Plates:** Locally sourced, seasonal produce is often more nutritious as it doesn’t sit in storage for long periods. Fresher ingredients lead to healthier, tastier meals.
2.  **A Greener Planet:** The environmental benefits of sustainable dining are immense. By reducing food miles and minimizing waste, farm-to-table practices play a pivotal role in fighting climate change.
3.  **Economic Upliftment:** Supporting local farmers means contributing to the livelihood of small-scale producers, strengthening the local economy. At Vanchu Hut, every ingredient sourced locally is also an investment in the community.
4.  **Unique Dining Experience:** Sustainable dining often connects diners with the story behind their food. At Vanchu Hut, we use local flavors in our signature dishes. This creates memories that go beyond just a meal.`
        },
        {
            title: "Challenges of Sustainable Dining and Solutions",
            content: "While sustainable dining is rewarding, it’s not without its challenges:",
            // Use subsections for Challenges and Solutions
            subsections: [
                {
                    title: "Challenges",
                     // Include bullet points using Markdown list format
                    content: `
1.   **Higher Costs:** Locally sourcing ingredients can sometimes be more expensive due to supply chain inefficiencies.
2.   **Consistency Issues:** The availability of seasonal produce can occasionally lead to inconsistencies in the menu.
3.   **Lack of Awareness:** Not all diners fully understand or appreciate the value of sustainability.`
                },
                {
                    title: "Solutions",
                     // Include bullet points using Markdown list format
                    content: `However, these challenges can be overcome with the right approach:
1.   **Educate Diners:** Restaurants can communicate the value of sustainability through menu descriptions and in-house events.
2.   **Plan Smart Menus:** Designing flexible menus ensures that seasonal changes don’t disrupt operations.
3.   **Collaborate:** Partnering with multiple farmers and suppliers eliminates overreliance on one source, adding stability to the supply chain.

At Vanchu Hut, we have tackled these challenges by building strong ties with local suppliers. We also educate diners by being open about how we source our food.`
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            title: "How to Support Sustainable Dining",
             // Include numbered list using Markdown format
            content: `Sustainable dining is a community effort that involves both restaurants and diners. Here's how you can do your part:
1.  **Choose Sustainable Restaurants** like Vanchu Hut, which prioritize freshness and ethical sourcing.
2.  **Reduce Food Waste,** whether at home or while dining out. Take leftover boxes and savor that delicious Chinese food again later.
3.  **Ask Questions.** Don’t hesitate to ask restaurants about their sourcing practices. It lets them know sustainability matters to you.
4.  **Plan a Visit to Vanchu Hut.** When you eat in or order delivery, you support sustainable practices. You also enjoy fresh and tasty food every time.

By being mindful of your dining choices, you can help contribute to a sustainable environment while enjoying some of the best food Ghaziabad has to offer.`
        },
        {
            title: "A Tastier, Greener Future", // Conclusion section
            content: "Sustainable dining is more than a trend; it’s a vital step toward securing the health of our planet and ourselves. With each bite at restaurants like Vanchu Hut, you’re investing in better food, better farmers, and a better future. To enjoy real Chinese flavors and support eco-friendly practices, book a table at Vanchu Hut now. Together, each flavorful meal can make the world a better place."
        }
    ],
    // Define Call to Action links from the DOCX
    cta: {
        menuLink: "https://vanchuhut.in/menu",
        reserveLink: "https://vanchuhut.in/reserve"
    }
};
---

<Layout title={blogData.metaTitle} description={blogData.metaDescription}>
    {/* Optional: Keep or adjust the top hero image */}
    <section class=" font-agdasima ">
        <Image src={heroImg} class="scale-100 w-screen h-[168px] transform -translate-y-[100px] md:-translate-y-[60px]  object-cover" alt="Header Image showing Vanchu Hut ambiance or relevant theme"/>
    </section> 

    {/* Breadcrumbs Navigation */}
    <nav class="flex px-4 mb-6" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <ol class="flex items-center space-x-2">
            {breadcrumbs.map((item, index) => (
                <li class="flex items-center">
                    {index > 0 && (
                        <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-gray-400 mx-2" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M7.293 14.707a1 1 0 010-1.414L10.586 10 7.293 6.707a1 1 0 011.414-1.414l4 4a1 1 0 010 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
                        </svg>
                    )}
                    {item.current ? (
                        <span class="text-gray-600" aria-current="page">{item.label}</span>
                    ) : (
                        <a href={item.href} class="text-primary hover:text-primary/80">{item.label}</a>
                    )}
                </li>
            ))}
        </ol>
    </nav>

    <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
        {/* Main Blog Post Image Placeholder */}
        <div class="relative h-[400px] mb-8 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-lg">
            <Image
                format="webp" 
                src={blogData.image} 
                alt={blogData.title}
                class="w-full h-full object-cover"
            />
             {/* You can add an overlay or caption here if desired */}
        </div>

        <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none mx-auto px-4 py-8 prose-headings:text-primary prose-h2:text-secondary prose-a:text-accent hover:prose-a:text-accent/80 prose-strong:font-semibold">
            {/* Blog Post Title */}
            <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">{blogData.title}</h1>
             {/* Optional: Publish Date */}
             <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8">Published on: {new Date(blogData.publishDate).toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}</p>

            {/* Table of Contents (Dynamically generated or manually updated) */}
            <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-12 border border-gray-200">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-secondary">Table of Contents</h2>
                <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 space-y-2">
                    {blogData.sections.map((section, index) => (
                         <li>
                            <a href={`#section-${index}`} class="hover:underline">{section.title}</a>
                            {section.subsections && (
                                <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-1 space-y-1">
                                    {section.subsections.map((sub, subIndex) => (
                                         <li>
                                            <a href={`#section-${index}-sub-${subIndex}`} class="hover:underline">{sub.title}</a>
                                        </li>
                                    ))}
                                </ul>
                            )}
                        </li>
                    ))}
                </ol>
            </div>

            {/* Introduction */}
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-8 text-lg">{blogData.introduction}</p>

            {/* Main Content Sections */}
            {blogData.sections.map((section, index) => (
                <section id={`section-${index}`} class="mb-12 scroll-mt-20"> {/* Added scroll-mt for anchor links */}
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-secondary mb-4">
                        {section.title}
                    </h2>

                    {/* Inline Placeholder Image for relevant section */}
                    {section.image && (
                         <div class="my-6 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow">
                            <Image src={section.image} alt={section.imageAlt} class="w-full h-auto object-cover"/>
                         </div>
                    )}

                    {/* Render section content with Markdown parsing */}
                    <div class="text-gray-700 space-y-4" set:html={section.content.replace(/\*\*(.*?)\*\*/g, '<strong>$1</strong>')
                        .replace(/\*(.*?)\*/g, '<li>$1</li>')
                        .replace(/^\d+\.\s*(.*?)$/gm, '<ol><li>$1</li></ol>')
                        .replace(/<\/ol><ol>/g, '')}></div> 
                    
                    {/* Render subsections if they exist */}
                    {section.subsections && (
                        <div class="mt-6 space-y-6 pl-4 border-l-4 border-primary/30">
                            {section.subsections.map((sub, subIndex) => (
                                <div id={`section-${index}-sub-${subIndex}`} class="scroll-mt-20"> {/* Added scroll-mt */}
                                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2 text-primary/90">{sub.title}</h3>
                                    {/* Render subsection content (will parse Markdown lists) */}
                                    {/* <div class="text-gray-700 space-y-2">{sub.content}</div> */}
                                    <div class="text-gray-700 space-y-4" set:html={sub.content.replace(/\*\*(.*?)\*\*/g, '<strong>$1</strong>')
                        .replace(/\*(.*?)\*/g, '<li>$1</li>')
                        .replace(/^\d+\.\s*(.*?)$/gm, '<ol><li>$1</li></ol>')
                        .replace(/<\/ol><ol>/g, '')}></div> 
                                </div>
                            ))}
                        </div>
                    )}
                </section>
            ))}

            {/* Call to Action Buttons */}
            <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-center gap-6 mt-12 border-t pt-8">
                <a href={blogData.cta.menuLink} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="bg-secondary text-white px-8 py-3 rounded-full hover:bg-secondary/90 text-center font-semibold text-lg transition duration-300">
                    Check Out Our Menu
                </a>
                <a href={blogData.cta.reserveLink} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="bg-primary text-white px-8 py-3 rounded-full hover:bg-primary/90 text-center font-semibold text-lg transition duration-300">
                     Reserve a Table
                </a>
            </div>
        </article>
    </main>
</Layout>

<style>
